National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan had a phone conversation with Colombian Minister of Defense Diego Molano and Chief of Staff to the Colombian President Maria Paula Correa. They emphasized the significance of U.S.-Colombia relations and praised Colombia's efforts in addressing climate change. They expressed a mutual commitment to finding a peaceful solution to the humanitarian and political situation in Venezuela. The discussion also covered the progress made in implementing the 2016 Peace Accord between the Colombian government and the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia guerrilla group, as well as the importance of protecting human rights.